# Popular Free and Open-source Distribution of the Python

Python has its own [IDE](https://www.python.org/downloads/), for Windows, Linux/UNIX, Mac OS X, Other.

## [Anaconda](https://www.anaconda.com/)
![](data:image/png;base64,)

I highly recommend Anaconda, not only for Python user, but also for R user. It is very powful and highly integrated. It could be selected as working environment for both PyCharm and Visual Studio code.

## [PyCharm](https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/)

One of the most popular IDE for Python and could be used to develop large Python projects. 

## [Visual Studio Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/)

Visual Studio Code is a source-code editor provided by Microsoft. Cool thing of Visual Studio Code is that it includes embedded Git control!
